SIMPLE: underlie
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underlie
<hw>Un`der*lie"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>underlicgan</ets>. See <er>Under</er>, and <er>Lie</er> to be
prostrate.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To lie under; to rest beneath; to be
situated under; <as>as, a stratum of clay <ex>underlies</ex> the surface
gravel</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be at the basis of; to form the foundation of; to
support; <as>as, a doctrine <ex>underlying</ex> a theory</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To be subject or amenable to.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The knight of Ivanhoe . . . <qex>underlies</qex> the challenge of
Brian der Bois Guilbert.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underlie</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Underlie
<hw>Un`der*lie"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To lie below or
under.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underlie</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Underlie
<hw>Un"der*lie`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>See
<er>Underlay</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 1.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underline</ent>⟦br⟧
